Race.SpecificTitle: PW Proposition -- 13.71 Mills Continuation - PJ - 10 Yrs.
Race.FullText: Shall the Parish of Tensas, State of Louisiana (the "Parish"), be authorized to levy a special tax of thirteen and seventy-one hundredths (13.71) mills on all property subject to taxation in the Parish (an estimated $754,000 reasonably expected at this time to be collected from the levy of the tax for an entire year), for a period of ten (10) years, beginning with the year 2018 and ending with the year 2027, for the purposes of providing court systems for civil, criminal and juvenile cases; expenditures for election expenses and other related costs; expenditures necessary to construct, repair and maintain governmental buildings and plants; general governmental insurance expenditures; expenditures for the temporary detention, custody and medical services of offenders; and expenses related to the operation of the office of the Coroner, said millage to represent a two and forty-one hundredths mills (2.41) increase over the 11.30 mills tax authorized to be levied through the year 2017 pursuant to an election held on March 31, 2007?

Race.SpecificTitle: Village of Waterproof -- 14 Mills - M&BOA - 10 Yrs.
Race.FullText: Shall the Village of Waterproof, State of Louisiana (the "Village"), be authorized to levy a special tax of fourteen (14) mills (the "Tax") on all property subject to taxation in the Village (an estimated $13,795 reasonably expected at this time to be collected from the levy of the tax for an entire year), for a period of ten (10) years, beginning with the year 2017 and ending with the year 2026, with the proceeds of the Tax to be used for any lawful corporate purpose?
